# Keep the docker build context small. The build only needs ./rpm-repo (the
# bucketed RPMs) and the Dockerfile. Everything else -- especially ./rpms (the
# multi-GB extracted scratch-tag RPMs, redundant once bucketed) -- would
# otherwise be shipped to the daemon as context and overflow the runner disk.
rpms/
.git/
*.md
*.sh
ethernet-vpnkit.sock
flat-*/
